<Layout
	title="About SeamossInsider"
	description="Why we started SeamossInsider and what we're about."
	pubDate={new Date('May 11 2026')}
>
	<h2>Why SeamossInsider Exists</h2>
	<p>
		I started researching sea moss a couple of years ago after hearing about it from people in the 
		fitness and longevity space. What I found when I went looking for real information was a mess — 
		contradicting claims, influencers pushing whatever brand paid them, and almost nothing aimed at 
		active adults over 40 who actually want to understand what they're putting in their body.
	</p>
	<p>
		Most sea moss content online is either TikTok hype or dry academic abstracts. There was no 
		middle ground — no straight talk about what the research actually says, what forms work best, 
		what the real benefits are for people focused on longevity and performance rather than just 
		following a trend.
	</p>
	<p>
		So I built SeamossInsider to be that resource.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Cover</h2>
	<p>
		We focus on the intersection of sea moss and real wellness outcomes — inflammation, thyroid 
		support, gut health, muscle recovery, and longevity. Our target reader is someone who lifts, 
		stays active, takes their health seriously, and wants information they can actually use — not 
		a sales pitch.
	</p>
	<p>
		Every article is researched, not just regurgitated. When we cite a benefit, we look at what 
		the science actually says — and we tell you when the evidence is strong versus when it's 
		still early. You deserve honesty, not hype.
	</p>

	<h2>What We're Not</h2>
	<p>
		We're not a supplement store. We don't push a specific brand. We're not here to sell you 
		anything — we're here to give you the clearest, most useful information on sea moss available 
		anywhere, so you can make your own informed decisions.
	</p>
	<p>
		If and when we recommend a product, it's because we've looked at it carefully and believe 
		it's worth your consideration — not because someone paid us to say so.
	</p>

	<h2>Stay in the Loop</h2>
	<p>
		The sea moss space is moving fast — new research, new products, new noise. The best way to 
		stay current is to bookmark the blog and check back regularly. We publish new research-backed 
		content consistently, with no filler.
	</p>
	<p>
		Got a question or a topic you want covered? The contact info is below. We read everything.
	</p>
</Layout>